<normalizedToken originalValue="Flörke">Floerke</normalizedToken>
ex Sommerf.) Zopf. Accordingly, they stated (pp. 286, 373) that a proposal for the conservation of the name with a conserved type (Germany, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Flörke">Floerke</normalizedToken>
, Deutsche lieh. 153 (UPS)) was to be made by Vitikainen in 1994, also noted by the latter (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="624">Acta Bot. Fenn.</emphasis>
152: 30. 1994). However, this proposal does not appear to have been published.
</paragraph>
